Krewe,

I've been watching an old (vintage 1970's) British crime documentary that is
being rerun on the History channel each week. Normally, it is about famous
British crimes but occasionally they feature US crimes. I guess they run out
of material.

In any case, last week it was about US serial killers and it detailed three
that were never captured which were all named ZODIAC. One was active in the
San Francisco area from December 1968 for about a year. In his letters to
local newspapers he claimed about seven victims.

The first letter was sent to three different SF papers and included with it
was an enciphered note. One page of these cipher symbols, a third of the
note, was sent to each paper with a demand that they be printed on the front
page. Each paper did that.

The authorities were unable to decipher the note, but a San Francisco school
teacher finally cracked it. It was not a simple task and it revealed no clues
that could aid the investigation.

I have a copy of the note. I taped the show and was able to freeze the images
of the pages and copy them down. Unfortunately, also included was a brief
description of how it was cracked and a partial showing of the plaintext.
There was enough that completing the 'solve' was no longer a challenge,
except for the mistakes in the text, that at first were quite confusing and
probably would make the 'solve' much more difficult.

If this is not news to everyone and if this has already been a topic of
review by members of the Krewe or the subject of a book, then this post has
been a waste of your time. So, in the words of Emily Latilla - "Never mind."

If however, there is a crew member who is not familiar with this ciphertext
and would like to 'give it a go' then I will break out my scanner and
'convert' the three part text into .jpg images (it is in letters and symbols
not all of which are found on the keyboard) and send them as a Zip file to
anyone who asks.

