Hi

I remember the ZODIAC scare well.  Everybody was concerned.

If I recall, the 8 November 1969 second letter was solved by Robert
Graysmith back in August 1979. He wrote an interesting account called
ZODIAC , published by Berkley Books, 1976, [ISBN0-425-09808-7]

He actually sent his solution to the Kent State Conference to Greg Mellon
and Eugene Waltz.

The cipher is a substitution -transposition with 65-different symbols in the
cipher with 43 occurring 5 times or less. It is essentially a Homophonic
with variations as WFF used to write. Only two the + and the B occurred more
than 10x. It was not the same type of cipher as solved by the Hardens. The E
had 10 different equivalents, S had 9 and A had 7. The backwards C and
multiple L's  were nulls. The key word was the name of the reporter at SF
Chronicle. The ciphertext is full of proper names. Two clues ( I can supply
more for those interested) are: the first 8 symbols are key and POSHT/ is an
anagram for the Detective on the case TOSHI

